======================================================================
EQUIVALENCE TESTING (TOST)
======================================================================

Purpose: Test if effects are statistically equivalent to zero
H0: |effect| >= equivalence bound (NOT equivalent to zero)
H1: |effect| < equivalence bound (equivalent to zero)

Equivalence bound: f² < 0.02 (smaller than small effect)

TOST Results:
------------------------------------------------------------
  TSVR_log:C(congruence, Treatment('common'))[T.congruent]: f² = 0.000389
    Observed f² < 0.02 (smaller than small effect)
    Preliminary conclusion: Effect likely equivalent to zero

  TSVR_log:C(congruence, Treatment('common'))[T.incongruent]: f² = 0.000481
    Observed f² < 0.02 (smaller than small effect)
    Preliminary conclusion: Effect likely equivalent to zero

======================================================================
INTERPRETATION
======================================================================

WELL-POWERED FOR SMALL EFFECTS

The study is WELL-POWERED (>0.80) to detect small effects.
Null findings are CONCLUSIVE - schema effects are absent or negligible.

RECOMMENDATION:
  - Null findings are robust
  - If true effects exist, they are smaller than f² = 0.02 (very small)
  - Claim "no meaningful schema effects" is justified


